tags: look what you made me do
summary:
today marks one year since @taylorswift followed me. twelve months. 365 days. 
one year ago today taylor made me the happiest...
body:
today marks one year since @taylorswift followed me. twelve months. 365 days.

one year ago today taylor made me the happiest girl in the world. I remember waking up and seeing the notification and hitting my head on a cupboard in excitement. I still can’t believe that I am tumblr mutuals with Tay?!?! Like?!?! Sounds fake right?!?!?

It has been a privilege to have been a fan of Taylor’s for over ten years now. Watching her grow as a writer, singer and person has been wonderful and I have grown up with her presence in my life.

This year, June 22nd, I saw Taylor live for the first time. It was the most magical day of my life. I had never felt so at home. I cried, I laughed and I sang till my throat hurt. I met my online friends that I had made because of taylor and I got to experience the most incredible concert of my life. I helped hand out the PROUD signs before the show and to see it work out and make you so happy was the best feeling in the entire world! (I did end up leaving the concert on a stretcher because I literally danced till I dropped but it was SO WORTH IT!)

Thank you for following me last year taylor, it happened during a time when I felt very depressed and just the simple act of following me made me the happiest I had felt in a long time. Since then you’ve liked quite a few of my posts too! I hope one day I can meet you and hug you and just tell you how proud I am of everything you’ve done and how thankful I am for you and your music that has helped me get through tough times. (Ngl I would do anything to meet Olivia and Meredith too like they are just SO MAJESTIC!!!!!)

I love you, forever and always,

Holly x

summary: My life is an emotional roller-coaster. But without fail I experience these emotions on a daily basis in a continuous cycle: ...
body:
My life is an emotional roller-coaster. But without fail I experience these emotions on a daily basis in a continuous cycle: 

First, I’m like, “yeah, Taylor Swift is so cool”. 

And then there are times when i’m like, “Taylor Swift is amazing, I love her so much”. 

And then there are the majority of moments when I’m like, “Taylor Swift is the most precious human being to walk this earth, I will love her until the end of time”. 

And then the cycle continues
